ssets.\" The \"+ assets\" refers to the brand asset files (PNG/SVG), which might have hex colors embedded. But these are binary/image files, not code. The rg check for raw hex wouldn't match binary files. And SVGs might have hex colors... let me check.\n\nThe prior feedback says \"SVGs already aria-hidden + currentColor.\" If the SVGs use `currentColor`, they don't have raw hex. Let me verify:\n\nActually, I verified earlier that the source SVGs exist but I didn't check their content. The prior feedback says they use currentColor. If they do, they don't have raw hex. The acceptance gate \"raw-hex only in tokens.scss + visual-state.ts + assets\" would pass. But if SVGs have hex colors... the prior feedback says they use currentColor. I'll trust this.\n\nOK, final answer: one medium issue about theme-color.\n\nHmm, wait. Actually I want to reconsider whether the theme-color issue is real. The plan says `--bg #0D0F17`. But is this actually different from the current `#0e0f12`? Let me check:\n\n#0D0F17 = rgb(13, 15, 23)\n#0e0f12 = rgb(14, 15, 18)\n\nYes, different. #0D0F17 is slightly more blue. The theme-color meta tag should match the app's background color for a seamless look. The plan changes the background but not the theme-color. This is a real inconsistency.\n\nAnd nuxt.config.ts is in the \"MAY touch\" list, so the plan CAN update it. It just doesn't mention it. This is a missing step. Medium.\n\nActually, I want to also consider: is `#0D0F17` close enough to `#0e0f12` that it doesn't matter? The difference is very subtle. But the plan explicitly changes the canonical color. If you're going to change it, do it consistently. The theme-color is a one-line change. Not mentioning it is a gap.\n\nOK, I'm going to also reconsider whether I should raise the `apps/mobile/visual.ts` path issue. Let me re-read the allowed paths one more time:\n\n\"ALLOWED WRITE PATHS: shared/visual/**, apps/mobile/app/assets/**, apps/mobile/app/components/Logo.vue, apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue, apps/mobile/app/assets/css/tokens.scss, MAY touch apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts / apps/mobile/app/app.vue / apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main.scss.\"\n\n`apps/mobile/visual.ts` is NOT in this list. But the prior feedback (HISTORY) says \"apps/mobile/visual.ts = export * from '../../shared/visual' (mirror api.ts).\" This was round 1 feedback that was \"incorporated\" into the revised plan.\n\nThe HISTORY represents feedback from prior rounds. If the prior round's critic raised this as an issue and the parent marked it as addressed (by incorporating it into the plan), then I should not re-raise it. The prior feedback explicitly endorsed `apps/mobile/visual.ts`. So the parent has approved this path. I should not re-raise it.\n\nBut wait - was the `apps/mobile/visual.ts` path an issue raised by the critic, or was it a suggestion from the plan that the critic accepted? Looking at the HISTORY: \"apps/mobile/visual.ts = export * from '../../shared/visual' (mirror api.ts).\" This is presented as \"Prior feedback incorporated\" - meaning the prior round's feedback included this, and it was incorporated into the revised plan. This could mean:\n1. The prior critic said \"you need to create apps/mobile/visual.ts as a mirror\" and the plan incorporated it.\n2. The prior plan proposed it and the critic accepted it.\n\nEither way, it was accepted in the prior round. The parent incorporated it. I should not re-raise it.\n\nBut the ALLOWED WRITE PATHS don't include it... The parent might have forgotten to update the allowed paths list. Or the allowed paths are the original constraints, and the prior feedback expanded them. I'll treat this as resolved per HISTORY. Not raising it.\n\nOK, final verdict: one medium issue about theme-color.\n\nActually, let me reconsider one more time. Is the theme-color issue really worth raising? The plan is a \"visual foundation\" plan. It's setting up the color system. The theme-color meta tag is a minor detail. But it IS a real inconsistency that a user would see (browser chrome color doesn't match app background). And the fix is trivial (one line in nuxt.config.ts). And nuxt.config.ts is in the \"MAY touch\" list. So the plan should mention it.\n\nYes, I'll raise it as medium.\n\nLet me also check one final thing: the plan says \"11. app.vue — add <VisualBackground/> as first child inside a relative wrapper; keep NuxtLayout/NuxtPage.\" But VisualBackground is auto-imported by Nuxt (components: [{ path: \"~/components\", pathPrefix: false }]). So <VisualBackground/> would be available without explicit import. This is fine. ✓\n\nAnd Logo.vue: same auto-import. If Logo is used in other components, it would be auto-imported. The plan doesn't mention where Logo is used. But the plan is just creating the component. Where it's used is P10/P11 scope. Fine.\n\nOK, I'm done. One medium issue: theme-color mismatch.\n\nWait, actually, I want to check one more thing. The plan says the acceptance gate includes \"rg Math.random apps shared none\". But the `shared/api/` directory might have existing code. Let me check if there's any Math.random in the existing codebase:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_10ccf33d6b5140f481dc6ed9","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /usr/projects/Диплом && rg -n \"Math\\.random\" apps/ shared/ -g '!node_modules' 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"===\"; rg -n \"fonts\\.googleapis|fonts\\.gstatic\" apps/ shared/ -g '!node_modules' 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"done\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"polza","model":"z-ai/glm-5.2","usage":{"input":1753,"output":16159,"cacheRead":15168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33080,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782865850084,"responseId":"gen_2183394647075459073"},"timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:33:47.029Z","cwd":"/usr/projects/Диплом"}
