igh issue I'm missing? Let me check the PROJECT_RULES more carefully:\n\n- \"Files ≤150 LOC\" — all files are within 150. ✓\n- \"backend source of truth\" — plan doesn't touch backend. ✓\n- \"NO Math.random for visual\" — plan explicitly says NOT doing Math.random. ✓\n- \"no Google Fonts CDN\" — plan uses local font stack. ✓\n- \"raw hex only in tokens.scss + fallback theme file\" — plan puts hex in tokens.scss and visual-state.ts (fallback). ✓\n- \"VisualState fields fixed (no OD1 lilac / OD2 seed)\" — plan uses existing VisualState fields, no new ones. ✓\n- \"Vue v-bind() in styles OK\" — plan uses v-bind(logoUrl). ✓\n\nNo PROJECT_RULES violations. Good.\n\nLet me check if the plan references any files that don't exist:\n- apps/mobile/app/assets/css/tokens.scss — to be created ✓\n- apps/mobile/app/assets/brand/ — to be created ✓\n- shared/visual/assets.ts — to be created ✓\n- shared/visual/scatter.ts — to be created ✓\n- shared/visual/visual-state.ts — to be created ✓\n- shared/visual/index.ts — to be created ✓\n- apps/mobile/visual.ts — to be created (mirror api.ts) ✓\n- apps/mobile/app/components/Logo.vue — to be created ✓\n- apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue — to be created ✓\n- main.scss — exists ✓\n- app.vue — exists ✓\n- nuxt.config.ts — exists ✓\n- shared/contracts/visual-settings.ts — exists, VisualState type ✓\n\nAll referenced files are accounted for.\n\nLet me check one more thing: the plan says \"Logo.vue: import logoUrl from '~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png'\". But the asset being copied is named `chubzik-logo.png` (renamed from `logo.png`). The `~/` alias in Nuxt resolves to `apps/mobile/app/`. So `~/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png` → `apps/mobile/app/assets/brand/chubzik-logo.png`. This is correct. ✓\n\nThe plan says \"VisualBackground.vue ... import each svg url via ~/assets/brand/<name>.svg\". The SVGs are magic-spark.svg, magic-curl.svg, etc. So `~/assets/brand/magic-spark.svg` → `apps/mobile/app/assets/brand/magic-spark.svg`. These would be copied from the source. ✓\n\nBut wait — the source SVG files are named `magic-spark.svg`, `magic-curl.svg`, etc. The plan says \"copy 7 assets (chubzik-logo.png + 6 svg)\". The 6 SVGs keep their names. assets.ts says `MAGIC_SVG_FILES=['magic-spark',...6]`. So the SVG names are: magic-spark, magic-curl, magic-orbit, magic-thread, magic-wisp, tiny-spark. That's 6. But the source has 7 files: logo.png + 6 SVGs. And the plan renames logo.png → chubzik-logo.png. So the destination has: chubzik-logo.png + 6 SVGs (same names). Total 7 files. ✓\n\nOK, I'm fairly confident in my 3 issues. Let me see if there's anything else.\n\nOne more: the plan says tokens.scss is ~115 LOC. Let me count the tokens mentioned:\n- 13 canonical color tokens\n- ~10 semantic aliases\n- ~10 legacy compat tokens\n- 9 variant tints\n- ~10 non-color tokens (radius, space, font, opacity, shadow, motion, safe)\nTotal: ~52 tokens, each ~1-2 lines = ~80-100 lines + comments. 115 LOC seems tight but possible. OK.\n\nThe plan says scatter.ts is ~95 LOC with a LAYOUT_TABLE of 6 items per detail × 3 details = 18 ScatterItem entries. Each entry is ~4 numbers + asset name. 18 entries × ~1 line = 18 lines. Plus type definition, assert block, self-check. ~95 LOC seems reasonable. ✓\n\nvisual-state.ts ~120 LOC: FALLBACK_VISUAL_STATE, ACCENT_CATALOG, visualStateToCssVars function, assert block. ~120 LOC seems reasonable. ✓\n\nAll within 150 LOC. Good.\n\nOne last check: the plan says \"apps/mobile/visual.ts — `export * from '../../shared/visual'`\". This mirrors `apps/mobile/api.ts` which does `export * from '../../shared/api'`. Consistent. ✓\n\nBut wait — the plan also says \"shared/visual/index.ts (~5) — re-export 3 modules\". So shared/visual/index.ts re-exports assets.ts, scatter.ts, visual-state.ts. And apps/mobile/visual.ts does `export * from '../../shared/visual'` which re-exports index.ts. This works. ✓\n\nBut apps/mobile/visual.ts is at `apps/mobile/visual.ts`. The import `'../../shared/visual'`