hat's OK in JSON.\n\nLine 2: `[medium]svg-import-strategy @## VisualBackground.vue → specify static import map or import.meta.glob; Vite cannot resolve dynamic ~/assets/brand/<name>.svg paths`\n- sev: medium ✓\n- rule: svg-import-strategy ✓\n- loc: ## VisualBackground.vue ✓ (well, the plan heading is \"9. apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue\" — using ## + filename is a reasonable reference)\n- fix: specify static import map or import.meta.glob; Vite cannot resolve dynamic ~/assets/brand/<name>.svg paths ✓\n\nLine 3: `[medium]stale-theme-color @apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts:31 → update theme-color from #0e0f12 to match new --bg #0D0F17`\n- sev: medium ✓\n- rule: stale-theme-color ✓\n- loc: apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts:31 ✓\n- fix: update theme-color from #0e0f12 to match new --bg #0D0F17 ✓\n\nAll good. Let me check the ≤120 char limit for fixes:\n- Line 1 fix: \"use `bun run` instead of `npx tsx`; tsx is not a project devDependency\" = ~70 chars ✓\n- Line 2 fix: \"specify static import map or import.meta.glob; Vite cannot resolve dynamic ~/assets/brand/<name>.svg paths\" = ~105 chars ✓\n- Line 3 fix: \"update theme-color from #0e0f12 to match new --bg #0D0F17\" = ~58 chars ✓\n\nAll under 120. Good.\n\nJSON output:\n```json\n{\"ok\":false,\"feedback\":\"[medium]no-verify @## Acceptance → use `bun run` instead of `npx tsx`; tsx is not a project devDependency\\n[medium]svg-import-strategy @## VisualBackground.vue → specify static import map or import.meta.glob; Vite cannot resolve dynamic ~/assets/brand/<name>.svg paths\\n[medium]stale-theme-color @apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts:31 → update theme-color from #0e0f12 to match new --bg #0D0F17\",\"phase\":\"plan\"}\n```\n\nLet me verify JSON validity: backticks are fine in JSON strings. The `~` and `<` are fine. No unescaped newlines (using \\n). No trailing commas. Three fields. \n\nActually wait — I should double-check: are backticks valid in JSON? Yes, backticks are regular characters in JSON strings. Only `\"`, `\\`